ALBERS_USGS = '+proj=aea +lat_1=29.5 +lat_2=45.5 +lat_0=23 +lon_0=-96 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs'

  st_transform(ALBERS_USGS)

  st_set_geometry(NULL)

Hierarchical clusters: THE MAIN CODE

MAXDIST = 200
Warning messages:
1: Unknown or uninitialised column: 'samplesiteID_n_ALT'. 
2: Unknown or uninitialised column: 'samplesiteID_n_ALT'. 
ALT_MAXDIST = 150
links_more_than_one <- links_df %>%
  filter(!is.na(Linked_lagoslakeid)) %>%
  group_by(Linked_lagoslakeid) %>%
  mutate(nsites = n()) %>%
  filter(nsites > 1)
lagoslakeids <- links_more_than_one %>%
  distinct(Linked_lagoslakeid) %>%
  pull()
links$samplesiteID_n <- NA_integer_
links$samplesiteID_n_ALT <- NA_integer_
for (id in lagoslakeids) {
  # pull these sites
  lk_pts <- links %>% filter(Linked_lagoslakeid == id) %>% select(samplesite_lat, samplesite_lon)
  filter_indices <- which(links$Linked_lagoslakeid ==id)
  
  # cluster
  dist <- dist(st_coordinates(lk_pts))
  result <- cutree(hclust(dist, method="complete"), h=MAXDIST)
  result_alt <- cutree(hclust(dist, method="complete"), h=ALT_MAXDIST)
  
  # assign these sites
  links$samplesiteID_n[filter_indices] <- result
  links$samplesiteID_n_ALT[filter_indices] <- result_alt
}
LETTERS2 <- as.vector(sapply(LETTERS, function(x) paste0(x, LETTERS)))
# calculating distance from cluster center to site, and mean distance for the cluster
links_dist <- links %>%
  mutate(samplesiteID_n = if_else(!is.na(samplesiteID_n) & !is.na(Linked_lagoslakeid), samplesiteID_n, as.integer(1))) %>%
  mutate(samplesiteID_CLUSTER = if_else(!is.na(Linked_lagoslakeid),
                                    paste(Linked_lagoslakeid, LETTERS2[samplesiteID_n], sep='-'),
                                    NA_character_)
  ) %>%
  mutate(site_x = st_coordinates(.)[,1],
         site_y = st_coordinates(.)[,2]) %>%
  group_by(samplesiteID_CLUSTER) %>%
  mutate(cluster_n = n(),
         in_cluster = if_else((!is.na(samplesiteID_CLUSTER) & cluster_n > 1), 1, 0),
         cluster_n = if_else(in_cluster == 1, cluster_n, NA_integer_),
    cluster_x = if_else(in_cluster == 1, mean(site_x), NA_real_),
         cluster_y = if_else(in_cluster == 1, mean(site_y), NA_real_),
         cluster_meandist = mean(sqrt((cluster_x - site_x)^2 + (cluster_y - site_y)^2))) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(site_cluster_dist = sqrt((cluster_x - site_x)^2 + (cluster_y - site_y)^2)) %>%
  select(-c(in_cluster, site_x, site_y, cluster_x, cluster_y, samplesiteID, num_samplesites, samplesiteID_n, samplesiteID_n_ALT)) %>%
  st_transform(4269) %>%
  mutate(cluster_lat = st_coordinates(.)[,2],
         cluster_lon = st_coordinates(.)[,1]) %>%
  arrange(samplesiteID_CLUSTER)

Histogram of distances between sites in the same lake.

heights = 0
for (id in lagoslakeids) {
  # pull these sites
  lk_pts <- links %>% filter(Linked_lagoslakeid == id) %>% select(samplesite_lat, samplesite_lon)
  # cluster
  dist <- dist(st_coordinates(lk_pts))
  clus <- hclust(dist, method="complete")
  heights = c(heights, clus$height)
}
hist(heights[heights < 500 & heights > 0], breaks = 100)

How many lakes have clustered sites in them?

8545 lakes, using 200m clusters. This number is inclusive of MN which we know accounts for 3159 lakes on its own, and the GLNC data which we are planning to remove a lot of (1327 lakes, some of which will be removed).

aggregate_sites <- links_dist %>%
  st_set_geometry(NULL) %>%
  count(samplesiteID_NEW) %>%
  filter(n>1 & !is.na(samplesiteID_NEW))
aggregate_sites_sf <- links_dist %>%
  inner_join(aggregate_sites, by='samplesiteID_NEW') %>%
  arrange(Linked_lagoslakeid, samplesiteID_NEW) %>%
  select(templinkid, Linked_lagoslakeid, samplesiteID_NEW, samplesiteID_n, samplesite_lat, samplesite_lon, legacy_samplesiteID, legacy_sitename, legacy_programname, cluster_meandist) %>%
  mutate(samplesiteID_LETTER = LETTERS2[samplesiteID_n]) %>%
  distinct(Linked_lagoslakeid, samplesiteID_NEW, samplesite_lon, samplesite_lat, legacy_samplesiteID, legacy_programname, .keep_all=TRUE)
